sentences: David Ingram (April 24, 1948 – March 10, 2005) was a Hollywood, California based studio session musician, songwriter and arranger.
Ingram was a founding member of the first Christian rock band Love Song with Chuck Girard in the early 1970s, and performed on the Elliot Mintz television show Headshop (1971).
